quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,"Kāf, Hā Yā, ‘Ain, Sād."
  19,2,"A reminder of yoursg Lord’s mercy towards His servant Zechariah,"
  19,3,"when he called out to his Lord a call in seclusion."
  19,4,"He said, “My Lord, my bones have become feeble and my hair is aflame with gray, and never, in calling upon You my Lord, have I been wretched."
  19,5,"And indeed, I am afraid of what my protégés will do when I am gone, for my wife has always been barren. So grant me from Yourself a guardian"
  19,6,"to inherit from me and inherit from Jacob’s folk, and make him, my Lord, pleasing.”"
  19,7,"“O Zechariah, indeed, We give you glad tidings of a boy whose name is John; We have never made anyone similar to him{1}before.”",footnotes:1:At-Tabari mentioned that some exegetes said that among the meanings of the Arabic word “<i>sameyya</i>” is ‘someone with the same name’, so they considered him to be the first ever to be named as such.
  19,8,"He said, “My Lord, how can I have a boy when my wife has always been barren and I have become decrepit with old age?”"
  19,9,"He said, “Thus said your Lord, ‘It is easy for Me, and <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza and Al-Kesa’i read it as: “…and We have certainly created you…”</span>
  19,10,"He said, “My Lord, give me a sign.” He said, “Your sign is that you do not speak to people for three nights,(despite) being in perfect shape.”"